    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a pristine 1995 Porsche 911 (993) Carrera, the final evolution of the air-cooled era. The M64/05 3.6-liter boxer engine operates with surgical precision, exhibiting flawless compression across all cylinders and a bone-dry crankcase. Power is managed through the G50/21 close-ratio 6-speed manual gearbox, ensuring tactile engagement and crisp synchronization. The chassis features the sophisticated LSA multi-link rear suspension, providing exceptional lateral stability and kinematic toe control. Brakes consist of ventilated rotors clamped by four-piston fixed calipers, retaining factory-spec hydraulic pressure. This vehicle is free of any electrolytic corrosion or thermal fatigue in the exhaust manifold. A turn-key investment for the collector who demands mechanical perfection.",
